<body>
  <div class="recipe">
    <div class="recipe--column">
      <div class="label">Recipe</div>
      <h2 class="title">Spaghetti Squash Boatsd</h2>

      <img class="recipe--img" src="https://place-hold.it/400x500" />

      <section class="section">
        <div class="hint">Ready in <strong>50 minutes</strong></div>
        <div class="hint">Serves <strong>4-6 people (depending on size of the squash</strong></div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h3 class="subheading">Tips</h3>
        <div>
          This is a very customizable recipe. You can add the vegetables and flavors you prefer. If you prefer, you can scrape out the cooked squash into a seperate bowl and add your sauce.

        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="recipe--column">
      <section class="section">
        <h3 class="subheading">Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1 spaghetti squash</li>
          <li>Vegetable(s) of choice</li>
          <li>Bean(s) of choice</li>
          <li>Sauce of choice</li>
          <li>Cheese of choice</li>


        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h3 class="subheading">Preparation</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <strong>Roast your squash.</strong> Cut the squash in half. Coat with olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.
          </li>
          <li>
            Roast for 40 minutes at 400 degrees. You might need extra time if the squash does not easily fluff up with a fork. A bigger squash will need about 10 more minutes.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Make your sauce of choice.</strong> For Italian flavors, saute kale with some minced garlic. Add in pesto and chickpeas.
          </li>
          <li>
            For Mexican flavors, saute corn and black beans with some taco seasoning. Add diced tomatoes and bell peppers.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Assemble and broil.</strong> Fluff the squash with a fork once cooked.
          </li>
          <li>
            Mix in your sauce of choice and top with cheese. Broil for a few minutes until cheese is bubbly.
          </li>
          <li>
            Let cool slightly and serve. Garnish with fresh herbs and maybe a slice of lime.
          </li>
          

        </ol>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>


</body>
